As of the 2010 census, Breinigsville consists of 51.11% females and 48.89% male. The population is made of 79.92% White Non-Hispanic, 5.24% Black or African American, 0.48% Native American or Alaskan Native, 11.07% Asian, 0.0% Native Hawaiian, 1.55% were two or more races, and 1.74% were some other race. Of the population 7.08% were of Hispanic or Latino ancestry.<ref name="Census2010">{{cite web|title=Census of Population and Housing, 2010|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/cen2010/cph-1-40.pdf|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=6 March 2014}}</ref>

The town has a population of 4,138 with a [[median age]] of 34.6. The largest age groups are 19.21% (5–17), 17.97% (25–34), 16.24% (35–44), and 12.87% (45–54). Breinigsville has 1,550 households made of 1,112 families and 438 non-family households. The average is 2.67 individuals per household and 3.16 individuals per family.<ref name="Census2010" /> Additionally, with 1,677 total housing units, 1,550 are occupied and 127 are vacant.<ref name="Census2010" /> 91.2% of households are owner-occupied and 2.34% rent.

